('2018-09-25 12:20:01', 'Not the best parador I have stayed in.

Free parking on the square was restricted because of the annual festival that takes place throughout September and parking in the underground garage was expensive despite the discount.

Because of the festival we asked for a quieter room. The room was at the back of the parador away from the square so was fairly quiet, was spacious and had with views over the countryside.

The restaurant and service was a bit pretentious with bigger pewter platters and domed covers that were whisked off to present you with your main meal. Despite being half board we had to turn up as soon as the restaurant opened to get a table every evening. With no booking system in place, people were being turned away and told to come back later. Not a very good system. Instead of having free access to the olive oil like in the other paradors,  you were just given a small dish of oil. The white bread (no choice!) was hard, stale and not easy to eat - you soon ran out of oilve oil to soften it. The food and wine were otherwise very good.

There''s not much to Lerma itself (the town walk in the early evening before dinner allowed us to see the best parts) but it does make a good base for visiting Burgos, Santo Domingo del Silos and other tourist attractions in the area.

Not a parador I''m dying to return to.', 'Hotel', 3, 'ChIJhUc9OvB3Rg0RMcS6OIzCfXM', 'es', 'Dear Customer, First of all, thank you for your time in sharing your experience with the other users of this community. Thanks for your review and your assessment. We regret very much that your experience in our Parador has not lived up to your expectations in the points that you detail. The first week of September is celebrated in Lerma local festivities, so the Parador is affected as far as noise is concerned as it is in the center of the town. We always advise all our clients about it, we also try to facilitate their stay if they still decide to come, assigning rooms far from the noise or even putting earplugs. Due to the holidays you can not park in the surroundings street or in the Plaza Mayor, but the Parador has an indoor parking service for guests staying for € 6 per place and per night. We regret that this price was expensive for you, but it is the alternative that we offer in the face of circumstances beyond our control. We are also surprised by what you tell us about the restaurant: the reception inform on arrival time to all customers the restaurant service, schedule and reservations, especially those who have half board, in addition to controlling reservations from the opening time (8:15 p.m. maximum time to reserve (22.15h), our restaurant closes at 22.45, but no customer has ever left without dinner. In all restaurant services there is the service of olive oil with bread, it is also a differentiated practice in our restaurants, with baked bread of the day. Again, we regret that your expectations have not been met by our services. We remain at your disposal for any question you may need. Best regards. Estíbaliz Martín. Reception Manager.', NULL),
